Derivation of name. Reflecting the high number of pulses in each chirp. Geographic range. Southern California, far southern Nevada, and southwestern Arizona ( Fig. 70 ), including on the Channel Islands of Santa Cruz and Santa Catalina. Also extends into Mexico west of the Continental Divide (
Weissman et al. 2009
) and throughout much of Baja California , Mexico (Weissman et al. 1980).
